      "span_text": "Exogenous IFN-g treatment promoted neuronal differentiation of HUCBNP As IFN-g inhibited HUCBNP proliferation, we next determined whether IFN-g affects HUCBNP neuronal differentiation as documented earlier for embryonic mouse cerebellum neural progenitors. On 14 days of treatment of HUCBNP with hrIFN-g, the cells undergo hypertrophy, transformed to a bipolar or multipolar or fibroblast-like morphotypes, expressing neurite outgrowths of different lengths (Figures 5a and b), as reported on treatment of neuroblastoma or PC12 neurons with hrIFN-g, resembling the morphological plasticity of neuronal cultures."
